## 🅿️ ParkingSpot

### Attributes
| Attribute | Type | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| spot_id | int | Unique identifier |
| size | SpotSizeType | SMALL/MEDIUM/LARGE |
| floor_number | int | Which floor |
| status | SpotStatus | AVAILABLE/OCCUPIED |
| vehicle | Vehicle | Currently parked (or None) |

### Methods
| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `can_fit(vehicle)` | Check if spot size >= vehicle required size |
| `is_available()` | Check status == AVAILABLE |
| `park(vehicle)` | Assign vehicle, set OCCUPIED |
| `unpark()` | Remove vehicle, set AVAILABLE |

### Key Logic: can_fit()
```python
def can_fit(self, vehicle: Vehicle) -> bool:
    # Spot size (1,2,3) must be >= vehicle required size (1,2,3)
    return self.size.value >= vehicle.get_required_size().value
```

### Example:
| Spot Size | Motorcycle (1) | Car (2) | Truck (3) |
|-----------|----------------|---------|-----------|
| SMALL (1) | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
| MEDIUM (2) | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ |
| LARGE (3) | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |

