## 🏛️ ParkingSystem (Singleton)

### Attributes
| Attribute | Type | Description |
|-----------|------|-------------|
| floors | List[Floor] | All parking floors |
| ticketing_manager | TicketingManager | Handles tickets |
| pricing_strategy | PricingStrategy | Fee calculation |
| allocation_strategy | AllocationStrategy | Spot finding |

### Methods
| Method | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `park_vehicle(vehicle)` | Find spot → Issue ticket |
| `unpark_vehicle(ticket_id)` | Calculate fee → Free spot |
| `get_available_spots_count()` | Total free spots |
| `is_full()` | Check if no spots available |

### Core Logic
```python
class ParkingSystem:
    _instance = None
    
    def park_vehicle(self, vehicle: Vehicle) -> ParkingTicket:
        # Find spot using strategy
        spot = self.allocation_strategy.find_spot(self.floors, vehicle)
        if not spot:
            raise Exception("Parking lot is full for this vehicle type")
        
        # Park the vehicle
        spot.park(vehicle)
        
        # Issue ticket
        ticket = self.ticketing_manager.issue_ticket(vehicle, spot)
        print(f"✅ Parked at Floor {spot.floor_number}, Spot {spot.spot_id}")
        return ticket
    
    def unpark_vehicle(self, ticket_id: int) -> float:
        ticket = self.ticketing_manager.get_ticket(ticket_id)
        ticket.exit_time = datetime.now()
        
        # Calculate fee
        hours = ticket.get_duration_hours()
        fee = self.pricing_strategy.calculate_fee(ticket.vehicle, hours)
        
        # Free the spot
        ticket.spot.unpark()
        
        print(f"💰 Fee: ₹{fee} for {hours:.2f} hours")
        return fee
```

